  "Notes": [
    {
      "Text": "Security update for zlib",
      "Title": "Topic",
      "Type": "Summary"
    },
    {
      "Text": "This update for zlib fixes the following issues:\n\n\n- CVE-2026-27171: Fixed an infinite loop via the crc32_combine64 and crc32_combine_gen64 functions due to missing checks for negative lengths. (bsc#1258392)\n- CVE-2023-45853: Fixed an integer overflow and resultant heap-based buffer overflow in zipOpenNewFileInZip4_6. (bsc#1216378)\n",
      "Title": "Details",
      "Type": "General"
    },
